The set S of all such positive integers n is given by:
\begin{equation*}
S=
\begin{cases}
    \{n | n=2 \text{ or } n-2 \text{ has an odd factor greater than 1}\}, & \text{if } k=1,\\
    \{n | n=2 \text{ or } n \geq 5\}, & \text{if } k=2,\\
    \{n | n=2 \text{ or } n \geq 4\}, & \text{if } k=4,\\
    \mathbb{N}^{+}, & \text{if } k=3 \text{ or } k \geq 5.
\end{cases}
\end{equation*}
